Description:
    Rebuild this template app's "mesh" setup for a new app name and production deployment.

Example:
    bin/rails generate mesh midwest_dads \
      --domain midwestdads.example.com \
      --github-username your-github-user \
      --server-ip 203.0.113.10 \
      --onepassword-account ABC123XYZ

What it does:
    1. Renames chat_app placeholders to the new app name
    2. Updates production SSL and URL configuration
    3. Generates a GHCR-based Kamal deploy config
    4. Generates a 1Password-backed .kamal/secrets file
    5. Writes or updates Personal/<new app name> with the managed secret set
    6. Ensures the deploy secret set includes SECRET_KEY_BASE without relying on Rails credentials

Options:
    --source-item             1Password item used as the bootstrap source (default: chat_app)
    --registry-source-item    1Password item used to source KAMAL_REGISTRY_PASSWORD when needed
    --skip-onepassword        Skip reading and writing 1Password items
    --vault                   1Password vault name (default: Personal)

Notes:
    - This generator expects to run inside this app template structure.
    - It does not migrate plinth generators or copy baseline deployment files verbatim.
    - Source-item fields with labels and non-empty values are imported into the managed secret set.
